  "prompt": "What is a normal waist size for a women?",
  "response": "The normal or healthy waist size for women can vary depending on age, height, and body type. However, here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. According to health experts:\n- A waist circumference under 35 inches (88 cm) is generally considered healthy\n- A waist circumference over 35 inches (88 cm) may indicate increased health risks\n\n2. Average waist sizes by age:\n- 20-39 years: around 32-34 inches\n- 40-59 years: around 36-37 inches\n\n3. Waist-to-hip ratio is also important:\n- Ideally, the waist should be smaller than the hips\n- A healthy ratio is typically around 0.8 or less\n\n4. Factors affecting waist size:\n- Genetics\n- Diet\n- Exercise\n- Muscle mass\n- Body composition\n\nRemember that these are general guidelines, and individual health can vary. Consulting a healthcare professional can provide personalized advice about healthy body measurements.",
